      "title": "How Apple Stock Has Fared Under Tim Cook",
      "description": "",
      "summary": "Apple stock has been an all-star performer during Tim Cook's career as CEO, but it hasn't been the MVP.  Shares of the tech giant have risen more than 1,900% since Cook was named chief executive on Aug. 24, 2011, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  Apple announced yesterday that John Ternus would succeed Cook as CEO, effective Sept. 1, with Cook becoming executive chairman.",
